WEBVTT

00:00:01.602 --> 00:00:03.302
(Episode 28)

00:00:04.742 --> 00:00:06.372
(Director Ko Seong Hui)

00:00:08.172 --> 00:00:09.682
(I'm sorry about earlier, for asking you to call me Mom.)

00:00:10.912 --> 00:00:12.082
What's going on?

00:00:17.522 --> 00:00:19.892
I'm sorry about earlier, for asking you to call me Mom.

00:00:21.322 --> 00:00:22.422
Call her Mom?

00:00:23.122 --> 00:00:25.161
Call me that when it feels right to you.

00:00:25.162 --> 00:00:27.532
I just want to hear it once before I die.

00:00:27.892 --> 00:00:29.002
My daughter.

00:00:29.562 --> 00:00:30.662
"My daughter?"

00:00:38.912 --> 00:00:39.912
Wait. Then...

00:00:40.872 --> 00:00:43.212
That woman was...

00:01:08.902 --> 00:01:10.072
My Eun Oh...

00:01:10.872 --> 00:01:12.242
met her birth mother?

00:01:13.512 --> 00:01:15.942
When? How?

00:01:18.782 --> 00:01:19.882
A client.

00:01:23.282 --> 00:01:26.252
Mom, I got a construction project worth 200,000 dollars today.

00:01:27.652 --> 00:01:29.492
Don't tell me they've been meeting ever since then.

00:01:30.892 --> 00:01:33.262
So Eun Oh wanted to find her birth mother.

00:01:34.462 --> 00:01:36.332
How long has she felt that way?

00:01:37.262 --> 00:01:38.802
Was it since what happened with Gang Oh?

00:01:40.902 --> 00:01:42.572
What am I going to do?

00:01:55.252 --> 00:01:56.322
Mom.

00:02:00.592 --> 00:02:01.592
Mom?

00:02:10.762 --> 00:02:12.302
(Mom)

00:02:24.882 --> 00:02:26.812
What's this? She left her phone.

00:02:31.922 --> 00:02:32.922
Mom.

00:02:37.062 --> 00:02:38.092
That's strange.

00:02:38.622 --> 00:02:39.732
Where could she have gone?

00:03:21.532 --> 00:03:23.802
He needed a liver transplant,

00:03:24.672 --> 00:03:27.312
but thankfully, we found a donor and scheduled the surgery.

00:03:28.572 --> 00:03:32.852
So what are we supposed to do now? There aren't any other donors.

00:03:34.312 --> 00:03:36.652
Does that mean he could die?

00:03:39.992 --> 00:03:41.722
- Hey! - You scared me.

00:03:42.562 --> 00:03:45.392
Where's Mom? Why are you praying over the stew?

00:03:46.232 --> 00:03:47.692
Hasn't Mom come back from the restaurant yet?

00:03:48.262 --> 00:03:49.562
She is back.

00:03:49.902 --> 00:03:52.332
But I think she just stepped out for a bit.

00:03:52.602 --> 00:03:54.172
She even left her phone.

00:04:00.472 --> 00:04:01.472
Mom.

00:04:02.312 --> 00:04:03.782
- Where have you been? - Oh, hey.

00:04:04.312 --> 00:04:07.312
Well, I was making stew and realised we were out of tofu.

00:04:07.382 --> 00:04:12.082
I rushed to the market for some, but I forgot my wallet.

00:04:12.152 --> 00:04:16.362
So, I guess we're having the stew without tofu today.

00:04:16.662 --> 00:04:18.262
How could you forget the tofu?

00:04:18.722 --> 00:04:20.732
- I know, right? - What?

00:04:21.292 --> 00:04:22.632
But the tofu's right there.

00:04:26.072 --> 00:04:27.172
So it is.

00:04:27.732 --> 00:04:29.572
Gosh, how did I not see it when I looked before?

00:04:30.802 --> 00:04:34.512
Mom, how many fingers do you see? Tell me, how many?

00:04:35.812 --> 00:04:36.942
Get out of the way.

00:04:44.982 --> 00:04:47.792
I've secured the capital for 52 percent of the shares.

00:04:48.052 --> 00:04:49.791
As for the remaining shares, I'll acquire 15 percent in year 1,

00:04:49.792 --> 00:04:51.092
then 25 percent in year 2,

00:04:51.322 --> 00:04:52.732
and the final 10 percent in year 3.

00:04:53.032 --> 00:04:55.032
I propose a phased acquisition.

00:04:55.862 --> 00:04:58.732
You'll oversee my progress as an advisor for three years.

00:04:58.902 --> 00:05:00.972
If I fail to deliver on this promise in three years,

00:05:01.402 --> 00:05:02.842
I will return the company to you.

00:05:02.942 --> 00:05:06.442
You want me to give up my company for only half the sale price?

00:05:06.512 --> 00:05:09.982
In return, you won't watch AP Group, the company you built, go under.

00:05:10.542 --> 00:05:12.612
Rumiko intends to absorb and gut AP Group.

00:05:12.682 --> 00:05:15.552
And for Yeongsin Paper, who knows how they'll corrupt its identity?

00:05:15.612 --> 00:05:18.222
I'm sure you're well aware of this, sir.

00:05:18.282 --> 00:05:22.692
What's the guarantee you'll preserve the company's integrity?

00:05:22.962 --> 00:05:25.492
Because you didn't get into business just for the money.

00:05:25.862 --> 00:05:27.292
It has to be fun for it not to feel tiring.

00:05:27.562 --> 00:05:28.862
Only then can you dig in persistently.

00:05:29.162 --> 00:05:32.672
And that's how you get results. I saw you say that in an interview.

00:05:34.502 --> 00:05:39.242
- The interview about the orphanage? - That's what we have in common.

00:05:39.542 --> 00:05:41.912
Because I also find joy in running and growing my company.

00:05:43.542 --> 00:05:46.151
I hear you've grown your company well.

00:05:46.152 --> 00:05:47.952
Still, don't you think...

00:05:48.012 --> 00:05:49.552
you're biting off more than you can chew?

00:05:49.622 --> 00:05:51.222
Because I couldn't bear to miss this opportunity.

00:05:51.882 --> 00:05:54.292
AP Group is the path I want to take anyway.

00:05:54.622 --> 00:05:58.622
I started late and had to be faster. But the fast pace made it exciting.

00:06:00.892 --> 00:06:03.962
Why did you discover your passion so late in life?

00:06:13.042 --> 00:06:15.412
Oh, did that punk really go see him?

00:06:18.812 --> 00:06:22.082
He certainly seemed determined enough.

00:06:25.052 --> 00:06:27.752
Yes. I came back from Cheongpo with this idea...

00:06:28.052 --> 00:06:31.422
for a DIY Interior Design Matching App,

00:06:31.692 --> 00:06:34.832
and that's when I found the work I was meant to do. And I loved it.

00:06:36.332 --> 00:06:38.132
Ditching your own wedding.

00:06:39.532 --> 00:06:41.102
You made quite the mess.

00:06:41.832 --> 00:06:46.042
- It's a choice I wouldn't make now. - And that's all?

00:06:46.742 --> 00:06:48.142
Are you done?

00:06:48.672 --> 00:06:51.782
Yes. I believe I've said all I need to.

00:06:53.982 --> 00:06:56.882
You've been watching too many soap operas.

00:06:57.382 --> 00:06:58.382
Excuse me?

00:06:58.452 --> 00:07:02.592
"An orphan who builds an orphanage, not wanting his kids to inherit..."

00:07:02.662 --> 00:07:05.692
And you come to me believing that from a 30-year-old interview?

00:07:06.132 --> 00:07:10.102
I built this company for 30 years. You think I'm not a ruthless beast?

00:07:12.132 --> 00:07:16.202
How could you expect to find the naive, passionate man I was?

00:07:16.842 --> 00:07:20.542
You waltz in with a magazine scrap you read when you were 26...

00:07:20.612 --> 00:07:24.612
and shove it in my face? Did you think I was some pushover?

00:07:24.742 --> 00:07:26.612
- Mr. Chairman, I... - Business is about money.

00:07:27.012 --> 00:07:30.682
Give up 48 percent and wait 3 years? Would you do that in my shoes?

00:07:31.422 --> 00:07:33.152
Cut the emotional appeal.

00:07:35.822 --> 00:07:36.822
I see.

00:07:38.522 --> 00:07:39.732
So, you've changed.

00:07:39.992 --> 00:07:42.061
I believed that once a person's values are set,

00:07:42.062 --> 00:07:43.762
they stick to them for life.

00:07:45.872 --> 00:07:46.872
And that just proves...

00:07:48.932 --> 00:07:51.072
- you're naive. - No.

00:07:51.772 --> 00:07:53.642
Why don't you just admit that you're the one who's changed?

00:07:55.112 --> 00:07:57.642
Good luck selling AP Group.

00:07:57.942 --> 00:08:01.982
In ten years, you'll see a company a lot like AP. When you do,

00:08:02.582 --> 00:08:04.252
take a look at the CEO's name.

00:08:11.022 --> 00:08:12.392
He's completely changed.

00:08:13.662 --> 00:08:16.262
Whatever. The whole AP Group makes me sick.

00:08:17.162 --> 00:08:20.572
Gosh, what a waste of energy. I can't believe I listened to Dad.

00:08:20.672 --> 00:08:21.772
Darn it!

00:08:25.002 --> 00:08:29.112
I advised my disrespectful son, whether he took it or not.

00:08:29.782 --> 00:08:31.512
I can't be the one to lose face.

00:08:32.342 --> 00:08:35.512
If I fail the practical exam, he'll look down on me even more.

00:08:39.622 --> 00:08:40.922
Is that Ji Hyuk?

00:08:43.362 --> 00:08:44.662
I'm home.

00:08:45.992 --> 00:08:48.092
- Ji Hyuk. - Oh, you're back?

00:08:48.192 --> 00:08:49.202
Ji Hyuk...

00:08:49.262 --> 00:08:53.172
Hey, it's no big deal. It's not like the company failed.

00:08:53.302 --> 00:08:54.502
I just crashed.

00:08:55.232 --> 00:08:58.802
But you didn't go to work and slept for two days straight.

00:08:58.902 --> 00:09:00.542
Of course, we were worried.

00:09:00.672 --> 00:09:04.282
Ji Hyuk, are you sure nothing's wrong at the company?

00:09:04.882 --> 00:09:07.382
Ji Hyuk, if something's wrong, you have to tell us.

00:09:07.752 --> 00:09:10.052
It's awful for us when we're kept in the dark.

00:09:10.322 --> 00:09:14.792
Guys, I'm telling you, it's nothing. I ran on fumes and crashed.

00:09:15.722 --> 00:09:18.022
I was trying to catch up on sleep without anyone knowing,

00:09:18.292 --> 00:09:19.662
but Dad had to make a fuss.

00:09:20.462 --> 00:09:22.562
You're sure nothing's wrong?

00:09:23.002 --> 00:09:24.762
Mom, look at my face.

00:09:25.032 --> 00:09:27.232
You're like a mind reader, Mom. You always know what I'm thinking.

00:09:28.402 --> 00:09:31.042
All right, he's fine.

00:09:34.542 --> 00:09:38.012
Next time, I'll just say that I'm so tired...

00:09:38.542 --> 00:09:39.552
I'm going to sleep for two days.

00:09:40.252 --> 00:09:41.412
I'm going to head upstairs.

00:09:48.452 --> 00:09:50.622
Gosh, that was so embarrassing.

00:09:53.332 --> 00:09:54.462
No, it's fine.

00:09:55.032 --> 00:09:57.302
I did everything I could. That's all that matters.

00:10:00.732 --> 00:10:02.842
So you didn't even have the guts to go, did you?

00:10:03.542 --> 00:10:06.312
You're jumping to conclusions again. I actually went.

00:10:07.942 --> 00:10:09.042
You went to meet him?

00:10:09.582 --> 00:10:11.742
I'm just coming back from my meeting with the chairman.

00:10:12.042 --> 00:10:13.152
And?

00:10:13.582 --> 00:10:15.912
What do you mean, "And?" I got completely shot down.

00:10:16.782 --> 00:10:19.592
I listened to you, and all I got was humiliation.

00:10:20.692 --> 00:10:24.262
It was a long shot anyway.

00:10:24.462 --> 00:10:27.662
You saw it through to the very end. That's what's important.

00:10:28.632 --> 00:10:31.232
Right. Of course, you've never run a business,

00:10:31.562 --> 00:10:33.032
so it's easy for you to talk.

00:10:33.932 --> 00:10:38.441
Hey! Do you have to taste something to know it's rotten?

00:10:38.442 --> 00:10:39.971
What? I may not have run a business myself,

00:10:39.972 --> 00:10:42.412
but I know enough business owners to know what's what.

00:10:44.342 --> 00:10:45.342
Fine.

00:10:46.482 --> 00:10:48.782
But I bet it felt good to get it off your chest, right?

00:10:51.382 --> 00:10:52.482
I guess so.

00:10:54.022 --> 00:10:55.592
Then that's all that matters. Good.

00:10:55.692 --> 00:10:57.922
What do you mean "all that matters?" I'm not okay with this.

00:10:58.222 --> 00:11:01.562
Then just try again. Honestly, this kid.

00:11:06.002 --> 00:11:07.072
Come on, Ji Hyuk.

00:11:07.472 --> 00:11:09.172
What do you mean you're not okay with it?

00:11:11.502 --> 00:11:12.712
It's all over now.

00:11:17.742 --> 00:11:20.852
Darn it. I shouldn't have told him that.

00:11:21.812 --> 00:11:24.482
Why did he have to listen to me this one time?

00:11:25.852 --> 00:11:27.492
Of all the things to listen to...

00:11:27.852 --> 00:11:30.092
I just made him look like a fool for nothing.

00:11:37.962 --> 00:11:40.332
What do you mean "all that matters?" I'm not okay with this.

00:11:45.142 --> 00:11:46.172
Ji Hyuk.

00:11:48.012 --> 00:11:49.612
What is it that you're not okay with?

00:11:57.182 --> 00:11:58.182
Right.

00:11:58.682 --> 00:12:00.452
As of today, Seong Jae is the new Vice President.

00:12:01.892 --> 00:12:03.962
- My goodness. Really? - Yes.

00:12:04.162 --> 00:12:05.892
Seong Jae, congratulations.

00:12:06.532 --> 00:12:07.692
Congratulations!

00:12:09.432 --> 00:12:12.002
Thank you. Thanks.

00:12:12.772 --> 00:12:15.802
Wow, you really surprised me, honey.

00:12:16.072 --> 00:12:20.212
You should've given me a heads-up. I would've prepared a party.

00:12:20.872 --> 00:12:24.542
Why make a fuss? It's just the next natural step.

00:12:27.312 --> 00:12:29.152
"The next natural step?"

00:12:30.052 --> 00:12:31.052
Oh, right.

00:12:31.622 --> 00:12:33.252
What's your schedule like today?

00:12:34.792 --> 00:12:37.322
How about the four of us grab lunch to celebrate?

00:12:37.622 --> 00:12:39.562
See? There you go again.

00:12:40.232 --> 00:12:43.302
The Magnolia Society meeting is today.

00:12:43.832 --> 00:12:45.162
Today's not great for me either.

00:12:45.632 --> 00:12:48.932
- Let's do it after the launch. - Right. I forgot about that.

00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:51.202
Okay, let's do that.

00:12:52.402 --> 00:12:53.442
What a relief.

00:12:54.212 --> 00:12:55.972
I had my heart set on getting some gopchang today.

00:13:05.252 --> 00:13:06.992
You're up 700 grams?

00:13:09.722 --> 00:13:10.722
Yes.

00:13:13.092 --> 00:13:14.962
Mr. Lee has been buying you snacks, hasn't he?

00:13:15.862 --> 00:13:18.432
How could you gain 700 grams just from eating salads?

00:13:19.402 --> 00:13:20.432
I'm sorry.

00:13:22.502 --> 00:13:25.372
A few days ago, I was stuck in traffic,

00:13:25.772 --> 00:13:27.812
and there was a vendor selling fish-shaped pastries.

00:13:28.572 --> 00:13:30.342
You ate street food?

00:13:31.112 --> 00:13:32.242
No.

00:13:32.812 --> 00:13:35.952
I was starving on my way out of the gym,

00:13:36.322 --> 00:13:38.182
so at the bakery downstairs,

00:13:39.222 --> 00:13:41.622
I got a pastry, a cream-filled bun,

00:13:42.092 --> 00:13:44.292
a canele, and some macarons,

00:13:45.092 --> 00:13:47.062
and we split them.

00:13:47.332 --> 00:13:49.232
Are you out of your mind?

00:13:50.232 --> 00:13:54.072
But I stopped immediately, and I've been working out every day.

00:13:56.542 --> 00:13:58.902
I'm very on edge these days.

00:13:59.402 --> 00:14:01.942
The last thing I need is you getting on my nerves, Yeong Ra.

00:14:02.942 --> 00:14:06.352
A woman's self-discipline should be as natural as breathing.

00:14:07.712 --> 00:14:08.712
I understand.

00:14:09.552 --> 00:14:10.922
Because of your father...

00:14:16.262 --> 00:14:17.422
Never mind.

00:14:26.332 --> 00:14:27.332
I'm so dead.

00:14:28.572 --> 00:14:30.602
Mom's going to make me weigh myself every day now.

00:14:33.272 --> 00:14:35.612
(Second date with Su Bin)

00:14:35.672 --> 00:14:40.912
(Second date with Su Bin)

00:14:42.652 --> 00:14:45.452
Meet me at 8pm by the parking lot at Yeonji-dong Mart.

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:46.622
Wear something casual.

00:14:46.692 --> 00:14:47.752
Something with loose sleeves.

00:14:49.122 --> 00:14:50.962
Something with loose sleeves?

00:14:51.992 --> 00:14:53.262
Man, where are we even going?

00:14:55.962 --> 00:14:59.162
Gosh, what a pain. It's a hassle to pick out an outfit.

00:15:06.472 --> 00:15:07.972
I'm craving beef gopchang.

00:15:10.642 --> 00:15:13.512
Fried rice made with it is so good.

00:15:14.052 --> 00:15:17.652
No. Starting today, you're back on the salad diet.

00:15:19.182 --> 00:15:23.122
You're right. Mom's going to make me get on the scale twice a week.

00:15:23.762 --> 00:15:25.321
- But, hey... - Gosh, seriously!

00:15:25.322 --> 00:15:29.192
Stop talking. I can't figure out the plot.

00:15:31.662 --> 00:15:32.662
Never mind.

00:15:33.132 --> 00:15:36.572
- I can eat it and work out, right? - Just drop it.

00:15:36.942 --> 00:15:39.742
Hey, you never know when your mom might show up for a surprise visit.

00:15:39.942 --> 00:15:43.112
That only happened because we never checked the app after installing it.

00:15:44.012 --> 00:15:45.782
Let's start checking it every hour.

00:15:47.982 --> 00:15:49.722
(Mom's Car, Guri, Yangpyeong)

00:15:51.222 --> 00:15:52.222
What?

00:15:53.022 --> 00:15:54.122
What? What's wrong?

00:15:54.722 --> 00:15:56.092
What? What is it?

00:15:57.162 --> 00:15:59.062
Mom has her Magnolia Society meeting today,

00:15:59.492 --> 00:16:01.262
so why is she heading toward Guri?

00:16:02.132 --> 00:16:05.962
- Maybe it's in Guri or Yangpyeong. - No way.

00:16:06.432 --> 00:16:10.642
It's a key corporate wives' meeting. It has to be in Gangnam.

00:16:11.472 --> 00:16:13.212
I think they even have a regular spot.

00:16:14.342 --> 00:16:16.272
Then where could she be going?

00:16:19.082 --> 00:16:20.912
(Mom's Car)

00:16:25.222 --> 00:16:26.952
Seojong-myeon, Seohu-ri?

00:16:27.992 --> 00:16:29.452
Why is Mom's car all the way out here?

00:16:31.122 --> 00:16:32.522
It's on the move.

00:16:40.402 --> 00:16:43.342
Hey, keep an eye on where it's going for me.

00:16:44.102 --> 00:16:45.272
Why? What are you going to do?

00:16:46.072 --> 00:16:47.072
What?

00:16:47.672 --> 00:16:48.842
I'm just going to check the comments.

00:16:49.942 --> 00:16:53.182
Hey, stop reading comments and work on your webtoon.

00:16:53.452 --> 00:16:55.682
Okay. Just five more minutes, then I'll start drawing.

00:16:56.052 --> 00:16:58.952
Everyone's dying to know what happens in the next episode.

00:17:02.852 --> 00:17:03.862
Finally...

00:17:06.322 --> 00:17:09.062
Okay, just breathe normally. Hold still.

00:17:12.302 --> 00:17:13.632
Okay, good.

00:17:27.812 --> 00:17:30.652
The liver scan reading is higher than last time.

00:17:30.722 --> 00:17:32.552
(Jin Seung Ki, Professor of Surgery)

00:17:32.822 --> 00:17:35.252
This is concerning. The waiting list is still very long.

00:17:36.662 --> 00:17:37.692
Excuse me, Doctor.

00:17:38.392 --> 00:17:40.162
If we find a compatible donor,

00:17:40.692 --> 00:17:43.162
my Woo Jin can get the surgery right away, can't he?

00:17:44.532 --> 00:17:47.972
Yes, but there's still a long waiting list.

00:17:48.332 --> 00:17:49.802
He has a younger sibling.

00:17:50.342 --> 00:17:52.802
His sister is coming to get tested for compatibility.

00:17:54.612 --> 00:17:57.112
Besides yourself,

00:17:57.182 --> 00:18:00.152
I thought you said no one else in your family could be tested.

00:18:02.112 --> 00:18:04.752
I found the daughter I lost long ago.

00:18:05.482 --> 00:18:07.552
She'll be coming in for the test.

00:18:09.762 --> 00:18:13.992
These are the results of a checkup she had recently. Take a look.

00:18:18.562 --> 00:18:20.072
Even for siblings,

00:18:20.172 --> 00:18:23.402
there's only a 25 percent chance of a perfect match.

00:18:23.772 --> 00:18:24.972
So please don't get your hopes up.

00:18:25.242 --> 00:18:26.242
No.

00:18:27.072 --> 00:18:28.542
I have a good feeling about this.

00:18:29.342 --> 00:18:32.282
But please don't let Woo Jin know about any of this.

00:18:32.912 --> 00:18:36.252
I want to tell him after the surgery is over and he's fully recovered.

00:18:36.752 --> 00:18:37.752
Of course.

00:18:38.122 --> 00:18:41.052
Getting his hopes up prematurely would only be more disappointing.

00:18:42.652 --> 00:18:44.262
If his condition keeps getting worse like this,

00:18:44.862 --> 00:18:46.762
what if he develops hepatic encephalopathy?

00:18:47.532 --> 00:18:49.292
The stress is killing me.

00:19:01.542 --> 00:19:02.612
Are you all right?

00:19:03.442 --> 00:19:04.542
I was worried about you.

00:19:04.612 --> 00:19:05.711
(Director Ko)

00:19:05.712 --> 00:19:06.782
(Are you all right? I was worried about you.)

00:19:19.932 --> 00:19:21.461
(Director Ko)

00:19:21.462 --> 00:19:23.232
Could you come over today?

00:19:24.332 --> 00:19:27.402
I have nowhere to grieve, and I can't even allow myself to.

00:19:27.832 --> 00:19:30.801
I've waited all day, and with so much to look into,

00:19:30.802 --> 00:19:32.602
I'm completely stuck here.

00:19:37.282 --> 00:19:39.112
She has nowhere to grieve,

00:19:40.152 --> 00:19:41.782
and she can't even allow herself to grieve.

00:19:46.552 --> 00:19:49.352
Okay. I'll head over right after work.

00:19:49.422 --> 00:19:52.062
(Okay. I'll head over right after work.)

00:19:52.362 --> 00:19:53.792
Wait, are you really going through with this?

00:19:54.232 --> 00:19:56.562
- So you're going for the final bid? - That's the plan.

00:19:56.662 --> 00:19:57.662
But, Mr. Lee.

00:19:57.962 --> 00:20:01.602
You said your meeting with AP's chairman didn't go well.

00:20:02.272 --> 00:20:05.642
- That's right. - Why are you still going for it?

00:20:05.942 --> 00:20:07.772
Because the bidding isn't over yet.

00:20:08.142 --> 00:20:10.581
Once you start climbing, you must reach the top, even if you crawl.

00:20:10.582 --> 00:20:11.842
Only then will you have no regrets.

00:20:20.052 --> 00:20:21.722
There you are, standing in that same spot again.

00:20:22.622 --> 00:20:23.622
Yes.

00:20:27.962 --> 00:20:28.962
About yesterday...

00:20:29.592 --> 00:20:31.932
I heard your meeting with AP's chairman didn't go well.

00:20:33.202 --> 00:20:34.472
Have you eaten?

00:20:35.632 --> 00:20:37.102
And if I said no, would you have a meal with me?

00:20:38.242 --> 00:20:39.942
Don't ask if you're not going to join me.

00:20:41.812 --> 00:20:43.072
Then why are you here?

00:20:44.112 --> 00:20:45.112
I came to give you this.

00:20:45.682 --> 00:20:47.252
I had some the other day. They're really good.

00:20:47.912 --> 00:20:48.912
You like hotteok, right?

00:20:54.522 --> 00:20:56.552
Why are you going to this trouble for me?

00:20:56.862 --> 00:20:58.022
What, you really don't know?

00:20:58.622 --> 00:21:00.932
I'm showing you I care because you're the woman I like.

00:21:03.162 --> 00:21:05.762
I thought we were done talking about this.

00:21:07.332 --> 00:21:09.172
I would never let someone like that into my life.

00:21:10.802 --> 00:21:12.542
Do you think feelings just end that easily?

00:21:13.512 --> 00:21:14.742
If it were that easy,

00:21:15.172 --> 00:21:17.412
then why did you insist on a reason back then?

00:21:18.082 --> 00:21:19.512
Why was it so important to you?

00:21:20.682 --> 00:21:24.582
For someone who knows how it feels, you're being so cold, and it hurts.

00:21:29.092 --> 00:21:33.062
Those feelings will fade in time.

00:21:37.102 --> 00:21:39.162
I have plans, so I should get going.

00:21:39.732 --> 00:21:40.772
You see, I...

00:21:41.572 --> 00:21:43.272
I'm going to see the final bid through.

00:21:44.942 --> 00:21:47.412
You're going for it, even though you know you'll lose?

00:21:47.742 --> 00:21:48.742
Yes.

00:21:53.142 --> 00:21:55.452
If you pull it off, I'll buy you a meal.

00:21:56.112 --> 00:21:57.122
That's a promise.

00:21:57.452 --> 00:21:59.021
I just said it to show you I'm rooting for you.

00:21:59.022 --> 00:22:00.322
Are you really getting your hopes up?

00:22:01.592 --> 00:22:02.592
I don't know.

00:22:03.292 --> 00:22:05.962
Anyway, I'll keep trying with AP until it works out,

00:22:06.662 --> 00:22:08.792
and I'm going to do the same with you.

00:22:09.192 --> 00:22:11.762
You just do whatever you want.

00:22:12.802 --> 00:22:13.802
Bye.

00:22:35.352 --> 00:22:36.392
Director Ko.

00:22:38.722 --> 00:22:40.562
Eun Oh.

00:22:41.892 --> 00:22:43.702
They said it was okay to go in.

00:22:44.032 --> 00:22:47.102
Of course. It's you, after all.

00:22:55.112 --> 00:22:56.172
I'm sorry.

00:22:57.742 --> 00:22:59.912
You look exhausted.

00:23:01.252 --> 00:23:02.952
I couldn't sleep at all last night.

00:23:06.352 --> 00:23:07.452
I'm just so upset.

00:23:09.292 --> 00:23:10.292
I can only imagine.

00:23:11.722 --> 00:23:13.192
And it's not just that.

00:23:14.632 --> 00:23:15.692
It's you.

00:23:17.102 --> 00:23:18.102
Me?

00:23:18.732 --> 00:23:21.032
We've only just found each other, and now this happens.

00:23:21.932 --> 00:23:24.172
Now that I've found you, I want to see you every day,

00:23:25.002 --> 00:23:27.672
but I can't even smile or be truly happy about it.

00:23:30.312 --> 00:23:32.442
That's understandable, given your situation.

00:23:35.012 --> 00:23:37.682
So what's going to happen now?

00:23:40.652 --> 00:23:42.192
I'll have to throw money at the problem.

00:23:43.592 --> 00:23:45.462
I hear there are people who can arrange that sort of thing.

00:23:46.292 --> 00:23:49.462
For a liver transplant, you must get a compatibility test,

00:23:49.932 --> 00:23:52.662
but the odds... If 100 people get tested,

00:23:52.902 --> 00:23:56.002
the chance of a match is only 1 to 3 percent.

00:23:56.532 --> 00:24:00.372
Even among siblings, it's only a 25 percent chance.

00:24:08.882 --> 00:24:09.882
Eun Oh.

00:24:10.582 --> 00:24:11.752
Would you consider...

00:24:14.222 --> 00:24:17.762
No. Never mind. It's nothing, Eun Oh.

00:24:19.462 --> 00:24:22.632
Why? What is it? Please, just tell me.

00:24:27.472 --> 00:24:28.472
It's just...

00:24:29.602 --> 00:24:32.442
Would you be willing to at least get tested?

00:24:36.042 --> 00:24:37.042
What?

00:24:39.742 --> 00:24:42.252
My husband doesn't know about any of this.

00:24:43.382 --> 00:24:45.352
He didn't want to be a burden on his stepfather,

00:24:45.752 --> 00:24:47.722
so he wanted to hide his illness.

00:24:51.722 --> 00:24:56.032
You've been dealing with this alone?

00:24:58.332 --> 00:24:59.502
At the end of the day,

00:25:00.732 --> 00:25:02.072
he's not his child.

00:25:13.142 --> 00:25:14.182
I'll...

00:25:14.752 --> 00:25:16.312
I'll get tested.

00:25:22.952 --> 00:25:23.962
You'd do that for me?

00:25:26.292 --> 00:25:29.632
I just feel like I have to do this so I won't have any regrets.

00:25:30.262 --> 00:25:34.202
Whatever it takes, I have to try everything I can.

00:25:36.132 --> 00:25:37.242
I'm his mother, after all.

00:25:42.512 --> 00:25:45.512
I can get tested first thing tomorrow.

00:25:55.792 --> 00:25:57.692
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

00:25:59.122 --> 00:26:00.122
Oh, dear.

00:26:02.092 --> 00:26:03.662
Why would she try to find them?

00:26:05.002 --> 00:26:07.001
- Mom, what did you say? - What?

00:26:07.002 --> 00:26:08.802
Oh, nothing. Just thinking out loud.

00:26:13.102 --> 00:26:16.612
I thought she was abandoned. Why would she want to find them?

00:26:17.212 --> 00:26:20.282
No. There must have been another reason.

00:26:20.552 --> 00:26:23.512
Did her birth mother show up? That's it.

00:26:23.582 --> 00:26:25.882
She must have shown up, so Eun Oh didn't have a choice.

00:26:26.782 --> 00:26:29.351
But she was abandoned with no record,

00:26:29.352 --> 00:26:31.122
so we could adopt her.

00:26:31.292 --> 00:26:33.222
How could her mother have found her?

00:26:35.732 --> 00:26:38.432
Right, Eun Oh must have registered her DNA.

00:26:43.642 --> 00:26:44.642
Gang Oh.

00:26:46.772 --> 00:26:47.772
Now,

00:26:48.372 --> 00:26:50.282
you really don't hold anything against your sister?

00:26:51.012 --> 00:26:52.012
What?

00:26:52.682 --> 00:26:54.812
Do you really see her as just your sister?

00:26:55.752 --> 00:26:56.812
Yes, of course.

00:26:57.182 --> 00:26:58.922
Then why did you act that way back then?

00:26:59.852 --> 00:27:03.862
When you found out she was adopted, you were just so cruel to her,

00:27:03.922 --> 00:27:05.362
and you were so angry.

00:27:06.022 --> 00:27:07.992
Mom, I already told you.

00:27:08.292 --> 00:27:11.062
I just felt so hopeless about my future back then.

00:27:11.632 --> 00:27:15.532
And it wasn't that I hated her. I was just hung up on blood ties.

00:27:17.242 --> 00:27:18.342
Blood ties?

00:27:18.502 --> 00:27:22.742
Back then, I wanted to get rich fast and hated working here.

00:27:23.112 --> 00:27:25.142
So everything just came down to money for me.

00:27:25.742 --> 00:27:29.012
"Blood is thicker than water." I was brainwashed by those words.

00:27:30.952 --> 00:27:33.822
"Blood is thicker than water?"

00:27:34.592 --> 00:27:38.762
Mom, when someone just snaps, they can act like a total psycho.

00:27:41.932 --> 00:27:43.862
After what happened with Gang Oh,

00:27:44.302 --> 00:27:47.272
I wonder if you felt differently too, Eun Oh.

00:27:50.872 --> 00:27:53.341
- Great work, everyone. - You too.

00:27:53.342 --> 00:27:57.112
(Shoealls)

00:28:04.852 --> 00:28:07.892
Where's she taking me that she told me to wear loose sleeves?

00:28:08.822 --> 00:28:10.022
Now, I'm really curious.

00:28:26.302 --> 00:28:27.712
This is cute.

00:28:34.712 --> 00:28:36.952
You know, you actually look prettier without makeup.

00:28:37.582 --> 00:28:40.152
No, I take that back. You look better with makeup.

00:28:40.722 --> 00:28:42.752
Make sure you wear makeup when you see your boyfriend.

00:28:49.032 --> 00:28:50.732
He said I was prettier without makeup.

00:28:51.302 --> 00:28:53.102
And he told me to wear makeup for my boyfriend?

00:28:57.902 --> 00:28:59.072
You're home.

00:29:02.412 --> 00:29:03.612
What are you doing home so early?

00:29:04.842 --> 00:29:06.242
I was just feeling a little tired today.

00:29:08.612 --> 00:29:11.422
Did you have fun at your Magnolia Society meeting?

00:29:11.552 --> 00:29:13.852
Do you think I go to those meetings to have fun?

00:29:15.522 --> 00:29:18.022
You need a lesson on your choice of words.

00:29:19.062 --> 00:29:20.732
You should ask, "Did you have a pleasant time?"

00:29:21.492 --> 00:29:23.802
That's the more refined way to ask.

00:29:25.032 --> 00:29:28.372
Did you have a pleasant time at your Magnolia Society meeting?

00:29:29.472 --> 00:29:31.172
We exchanged some useful information.

00:29:32.372 --> 00:29:34.072
Mom's lying.

00:29:35.042 --> 00:29:36.342
I'll see you at dinner.

00:29:37.072 --> 00:29:38.082
Okay.

00:29:49.892 --> 00:29:51.522
I'm so curious.

00:29:51.992 --> 00:29:53.692
Why would Mom have gone to Yangpyeong?

00:29:58.632 --> 00:30:00.002
I have to find out what's going on.

00:30:03.502 --> 00:30:06.002
Just park the car. It's right here.

00:30:07.372 --> 00:30:10.212
Seriously? The place she picked is just a cafe?

00:30:12.312 --> 00:30:13.912
Well, that's anticlimactic, Su Bin.

00:30:16.012 --> 00:30:17.012
Hey!

00:30:27.992 --> 00:30:31.202
- Hey, did you eat yet? - Yes, I ate at home.

00:30:31.262 --> 00:30:32.262
At home?

00:30:32.662 --> 00:30:34.932
I thought you wanted to meet at 8pm because you were busy.

00:30:35.032 --> 00:30:38.742
The launch is keeping you busy. You've eaten too, right?

00:30:39.072 --> 00:30:42.372
Yes, of course. The team and I ordered in.

00:30:43.712 --> 00:30:46.542
Wait, so she suggested 8pm just for me?

00:30:52.782 --> 00:30:57.292
Why the look? If we meet at 8pm, we get 4 hours until midnight.

00:30:58.122 --> 00:30:59.192
It's nothing.

00:30:59.492 --> 00:31:02.762
It's just that tea at 8pm seemed lame. That's why.

00:31:03.292 --> 00:31:05.432
Oh, really? Well, that's not what we're doing.

00:31:05.762 --> 00:31:06.762
Come on!

00:31:11.842 --> 00:31:14.612
Hey. What is this place?

00:31:15.542 --> 00:31:16.712
A knitting shop?

00:31:16.912 --> 00:31:20.682
Today's activity is knitting scarves to exchange with each other.

00:31:20.982 --> 00:31:22.952
You want me to knit?

00:31:24.052 --> 00:31:26.652
- Come on, Su Bin. This is too much. - Hey.

00:31:27.222 --> 00:31:30.792
Didn't we agree that I'd be the one choosing where we go?

00:31:31.192 --> 00:31:33.622
I know, but it's still a bit much, you know?

00:31:33.722 --> 00:31:35.692
You might change your mind once you try it.

00:31:35.992 --> 00:31:38.632
We're not allowed to go home until we finish these.

00:31:39.532 --> 00:31:42.432
Let's each pick the colour we want. I want...

00:31:43.102 --> 00:31:44.172
yellow.

00:31:45.172 --> 00:31:46.272
For me...

00:31:47.002 --> 00:31:48.072
I'm good with anything.

00:31:48.942 --> 00:31:52.182
Anything's fine? Then I'll pick one out for you.

00:31:54.282 --> 00:31:56.412
I think you'd look good in any of them, but...

00:32:00.552 --> 00:32:02.592
What? Is this one too bright?

00:32:04.022 --> 00:32:05.562
What's your personal colour?

00:32:06.422 --> 00:32:08.362
I don't know. I've never done that test.

00:32:10.602 --> 00:32:14.432
- You said you liked yellow, right? - Yes. You put it in like this,

00:32:15.772 --> 00:32:16.902
then loop it around.

00:32:17.442 --> 00:32:20.202
- Okay, hold on. In like this... - Loop.

00:32:20.272 --> 00:32:21.272
And loop.

00:32:23.672 --> 00:32:26.842
Su Bin. How about I just buy you a scarf?

00:32:27.852 --> 00:32:31.982
Look. Do you think the people here can't afford to buy a scarf,

00:32:32.052 --> 00:32:33.722
so that's why they're knitting?

00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:39.362
I know, right? Why is everyone here doing this?

00:32:39.762 --> 00:32:43.332
Just try it. You'll get it once you're finished.

00:32:43.592 --> 00:32:46.202
Why? What, because you're some...

00:32:46.262 --> 00:32:48.832
third-generation heir, you can't do this sort of thing?

00:32:49.302 --> 00:32:52.372
What are you talking about? That's ridiculous.

00:32:53.142 --> 00:32:54.242
Show me again.

00:32:55.272 --> 00:32:56.972
If I put my mind to it, I can do anything.

00:32:58.512 --> 00:33:00.142
It'll be easier if we're looking from the same angle.

00:33:00.512 --> 00:33:01.552
Look.

00:33:04.122 --> 00:33:05.122
See? Like this.

00:33:15.562 --> 00:33:20.002
He has nice hands, too. His fingers are so long.

00:33:22.572 --> 00:33:24.272
And his eyelashes are long, too.

00:33:27.872 --> 00:33:30.242
So that's what he looks like when he smiles without realising it.

00:33:30.812 --> 00:33:31.812
What?

00:33:33.042 --> 00:33:34.482
Su Bin, look at this.

00:33:35.352 --> 00:33:38.252
What? Oh, okay.

00:33:39.922 --> 00:33:40.922
You dropped a stitch.

00:33:44.922 --> 00:33:47.122
In and loop.

00:33:51.132 --> 00:33:53.862
Yes, right here. This part! How did you do this?

00:34:19.592 --> 00:34:20.592
I'm all done.

00:34:23.292 --> 00:34:25.302
- Hey! Wait, stay just like that! - What?

00:34:26.702 --> 00:34:27.702
Okay.

00:34:31.702 --> 00:34:33.802
Wow, you're a real natural at this.

00:34:35.212 --> 00:34:38.412
- Hey, this is kind of fun... - Excuse me, we'll be closing soon.

00:34:38.812 --> 00:34:39.812
Okay.

00:34:40.142 --> 00:34:41.152
Okay.

00:34:43.482 --> 00:34:44.952
Wow, it's that late already?

00:34:46.152 --> 00:34:48.052
Why haven't you gotten much done? What were you doing?

00:34:48.752 --> 00:34:50.592
You're just a really fast knitter.

00:34:51.422 --> 00:34:53.792
I'll finish this and give it to you on our next date.

00:34:55.232 --> 00:34:57.032
Didn't you say you couldn't go home until you finished?

00:35:00.562 --> 00:35:01.872
So, does that mean I don't have to go home?

00:35:08.012 --> 00:35:09.012
Let's go home.

00:35:14.512 --> 00:35:15.512
That's pretty cool.

00:35:16.352 --> 00:35:19.082
Time flies when you do this. It's more fun than I thought.

00:35:19.452 --> 00:35:22.722
- It's great for clearing your head. - Right? It's great for de-stressing.

00:35:24.052 --> 00:35:25.422
So is that why you wanted to come here today?

00:35:25.992 --> 00:35:29.062
Yes. You've had a lot on your mind lately.

00:35:29.232 --> 00:35:32.862
When something big is coming up, your thoughts get tangled, right?

00:35:35.972 --> 00:35:39.302
Thanks. You really helped me clear my head.

00:35:39.702 --> 00:35:43.212
Really? Yes! Today's date was a success!

00:35:45.182 --> 00:35:47.282
Here. An early Christmas present.

00:35:48.382 --> 00:35:49.782
An early Christmas present?

00:35:51.652 --> 00:35:53.822
So he's saying he doesn't want to see me on Christmas.

00:36:00.362 --> 00:36:01.362
Did you have fun too?

00:36:04.302 --> 00:36:06.102
Yes, totally.

00:36:08.302 --> 00:36:11.702
Me too. Come on. I'll take you home today.

00:36:13.102 --> 00:36:14.102
Really?

00:36:49.112 --> 00:36:50.112
That's two down.

00:36:52.142 --> 00:36:53.212
One more to go.

00:37:05.292 --> 00:37:07.222
What a lame date. So lame.

00:37:09.692 --> 00:37:10.832
I mean...

00:37:11.462 --> 00:37:14.832
How can I see her as a woman if I don't even get to look at her?

00:37:15.732 --> 00:37:17.902
Knitting to clear my head? What kind of date is that?

00:37:19.572 --> 00:37:20.572
Unbelievable.

00:37:28.282 --> 00:37:29.282
Gosh, whatever.

00:37:30.552 --> 00:37:32.052
I only have to go out with her...

00:37:32.922 --> 00:37:34.182
one more time, and then I'm done.

00:37:46.902 --> 00:37:47.902
Mom, I'm sorry.

00:37:48.532 --> 00:37:50.972
I absolutely have to be at the construction site today.

00:37:52.202 --> 00:37:54.772
I know. You told me last night.

00:37:56.812 --> 00:37:57.812
Good luck.

00:37:57.882 --> 00:38:01.712
Don't worry, I'll be fine. It'd be overkill if you came anyway.

00:38:03.912 --> 00:38:07.282
- Okay, I'll get going then. - Okay.

00:38:13.492 --> 00:38:15.232
She's probably going to see her birth mother.

00:38:16.662 --> 00:38:19.732
It's not like Eun Oh to miss something this important.

00:38:25.272 --> 00:38:28.442
(Cheong Ah University Hospital)

00:38:32.182 --> 00:38:35.452
When you get to the hospital, you'll meet with a doctor first.

00:38:36.112 --> 00:38:37.882
They'll ask for your consent and things like that.

00:38:41.422 --> 00:38:43.222
(Damga)

00:38:43.322 --> 00:38:44.862
I'm so nervous.

00:38:45.122 --> 00:38:47.461
Hey, I'm supposed to be the nervous one.

00:38:47.462 --> 00:38:49.532
You started this, and you're making me more nervous.

00:38:50.092 --> 00:38:51.562
I wish Eun Oh were here.

00:38:52.032 --> 00:38:54.002
I know, Mom. Even though my sister is tiny,

00:38:54.062 --> 00:38:58.042
she seemed so big in Dad's role. So bold and fearless.

00:38:59.242 --> 00:39:00.272
That's enough.

00:39:02.212 --> 00:39:03.742
Yes, you can come in now.

00:39:04.612 --> 00:39:05.612
Okay.

00:39:08.652 --> 00:39:10.882
(Damga Corp, R and D Center)

00:39:23.492 --> 00:39:25.432
Looking at these ingredients, this must be your secret recipe.

00:39:26.062 --> 00:39:28.232
Yes. I marinate it once with this,

00:39:28.632 --> 00:39:31.672
and a second time with this special marinade.

00:39:31.772 --> 00:39:34.412
The natural enzymes must've deepened the meat's flavour.

00:39:35.142 --> 00:39:39.142
It was exceptionally tender before. I was curious what the secret was.

00:39:39.342 --> 00:39:41.612
If this dish gets chosen,

00:39:41.912 --> 00:39:44.622
I'll reveal the secret ingredient ratios then.

00:39:45.552 --> 00:39:48.592
It's a healthy method, so customers can enjoy it worry-free.

00:39:49.122 --> 00:39:51.692
Exactly. These days, food must be more than delicious.

00:39:51.762 --> 00:39:53.192
