The more I read this, the more fascinating it gets.

00:41:23.582 --> 00:41:24.752
Tell me about it.

00:41:25.622 --> 00:41:27.452
I was embarrassed at first,

00:41:28.052 --> 00:41:30.052
but here I am reading these with you.

00:41:31.722 --> 00:41:32.822
Wait a second. What's this?

00:41:33.562 --> 00:41:34.662
What does this say?

00:41:35.032 --> 00:41:38.432
Hello. I'm the vice president of the Senior Model Association.

00:41:38.702 --> 00:41:43.072
I think the woman in your video would make a great senior model.

00:41:43.172 --> 00:41:47.242
If she's interested, please have her contact us at this number.

00:41:47.302 --> 00:41:49.572
What is this saying?

00:41:53.412 --> 00:41:58.422
Oh, my! They're asking you to be a senior model, Ok Rye!

00:41:58.482 --> 00:42:00.782
Oh, my goodness. No way.

00:42:01.622 --> 00:42:02.622
Oh, dear.

00:42:02.692 --> 00:42:03.792
(Jamun Medical Devices)

00:42:03.852 --> 00:42:05.062
Welcome.

00:42:05.892 --> 00:42:07.392
Could you take care of this customer for a moment?

00:42:07.692 --> 00:42:09.162
Yes, I'll give it a try.

00:42:10.262 --> 00:42:11.262
Welcome.

00:42:12.362 --> 00:42:14.602
Well, my mother-in-law mentioned this,

00:42:15.202 --> 00:42:17.102
and I was thinking of getting one for my father.

00:42:17.732 --> 00:42:19.972
In that case, why don't you try this first?

00:42:20.342 --> 00:42:21.342
Here, please lie down.

00:42:21.772 --> 00:42:23.142
Come on, Dad. Lie down.

00:42:23.912 --> 00:42:26.182
This is an eco-friendly product.

00:42:26.782 --> 00:42:27.782
It's nice and warm, isn't it?

00:42:28.152 --> 00:42:29.782
Oh, my. That's nice and warm.

00:42:30.452 --> 00:42:33.922
What do you call it? It feels like it's improving my circulation.

00:42:34.952 --> 00:42:37.152
My mother-in-law gets a lot of use out of hers.

00:42:38.062 --> 00:42:39.762
Dad, what do you think?

00:42:40.262 --> 00:42:41.262
Do you like it?

00:42:42.792 --> 00:42:46.362
If you keep using it, it'll help with your aches and pains.

00:42:47.562 --> 00:42:48.602
Let's get it then, Dad.

00:42:49.172 --> 00:42:50.172
I'll buy it for you.

00:42:54.402 --> 00:42:58.282
Depression is no big deal. It happens when you get old.

00:42:59.642 --> 00:43:01.182
At my age,

00:43:02.182 --> 00:43:03.552
nothing ever happens.

00:43:03.912 --> 00:43:06.252
So you just naturally start to feel down.

00:43:16.392 --> 00:43:17.392
Come on, Da Jeong.

00:43:18.002 --> 00:43:19.332
Why do you care what Gyeong Hun thinks?

00:43:20.332 --> 00:43:22.502
You just saw a daughter taking such good care of her father.

00:43:23.202 --> 00:43:25.202
I'm supposed to leave mine alone while he's on antidepressants?

00:43:31.312 --> 00:43:32.312
Gyeong Hun.

00:43:32.882 --> 00:43:33.882
It's me, your sister.

00:43:34.712 --> 00:43:36.982
I'm texting because we need to talk about something important.

00:43:38.852 --> 00:43:41.652
You know Dad's turning 90 soon.

00:43:52.062 --> 00:43:55.072
And he's been living alone for ten years now.

00:43:55.932 --> 00:43:57.202
(Gyeong Hun)

00:43:57.272 --> 00:44:00.502
You know it's not possible for me to take him in,

00:44:01.642 --> 00:44:03.742
so to make sure Dad isn't lonely in his final years,

00:44:05.412 --> 00:44:06.982
do you think you could have him move in with you?

00:44:07.712 --> 00:44:08.712
Give me that.

00:44:09.712 --> 00:44:11.522
Wait, what is this?

00:44:12.082 --> 00:44:13.082
What are you talking about?

00:44:13.882 --> 00:44:15.452
Did you really plan to send your father...

00:44:15.752 --> 00:44:18.192
